div.p:
Against this progress, a large number of important issues remain to be resolved in the Geneva negotiating session. These include:
—guarantees for unimpeded transit through, over and under straits use for international navigation;
—jurisdiction to set and enforce standards for the protection of the marine environment, particularly jurisdiction with respect to vessel-source pollution;
—rights and duties concerning marine scientific research;
—rights to mineral resources of the continental margin when such margins extend beyond 200 miles from the coast;
—the nature, scope, structure and function of the new organization dealing with the resources of the seabed beyond national jurisdiction.
